The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 6: A high-level committee has made a strong pitch for expediting reforms in financial services by suggesting the setting up of a financial development council under the chairmanship of the finance minister. The main focus of the council will be macro risk assessment and development issues, said the draft report of the committee on financial sector reforms set up by the Planning Commission.                             
	 Mumbai, April 6: A Reliance Globalcom official said the Dubai Port Trust authorities have impounded two ships, MV Hounslow and MT Ann, which were believed to be responsible for undersea cable damage that crippled Internet services in India earlier this year.                            
	 New Delhi, April 6: ONGC Videsh will sign an agreement on April 8 to acquire a 40 per cent stake in Venezuelas San Cristobal oilfield. ONGC Videsh will sign the agreement with Petroleos de Venezuela, which will hold the remaining 60 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, April 6: Fertiliser and chemical minister Ram Vilas Paswan has sought trebling fertiliser subsidies to over Rs 90,000 crore in a letter to Prime Minister Manmohan Singh.                            
	 Mumbai, April 6: The government has lost more than $100 billion because of the fall in the share prices of publicly traded companies where it had promoter equity. The governments stock market kitty accounts for over one-fifth of the total loss of about $500.                                                                                                                         
